definitions.definition: A food preparation common in southern India and Sri Lanka , made of vegetables and lentils (usually pigeon peas , also called toor dal ) in a spicy tamarind and lentil flour soup base.

main_definition: ( cooking ) A food preparation common in southern India and Sri Lanka , made of vegetables and lentils (usually pigeon peas , also called toor dal ) in a spicy tamarind and lentil flour soup base.
